ece30e36-a073-5d5b-a139-6116517b7e98,tg:rubgr:1544,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[recto] Conversion of Paul. In L. van Leyden's print the conversion (Paulus blinded by divine ray) in background; in foreground the soldiers (with the blind Paul); B. [Berthold] Riehl, Geschichte des Sittenbildes in der deutschen Kunst bis zum Tode Pieter Breughel des Älteren, Berlin & Stuttgart [Spemann], 1884, citaat p. 89; [verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: F.G. The composition of Bruegel's picture in fact developed from Lucas: The event placed in mountainous country; the rock rising steeply and at the [onleesbaar] a hidden view in the distant land below; also the procession as such, though this treated relief-like [onleesbaar] leading into depth, but some of the figures half hidden by & emerging from the rocks. A painting of the subject by P.B.II strongly influenced by L's print (see Lucas exh. [= B.L.D. (ed.),  Lucas van Leyden en tijdgenoten], Rotterdam 1952, N° 20).",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[recto] Conversion of Paul. In L. van Leyden's print the conversion (Paulus blinded by divine ray) in background; in foreground the soldiers (with the blind Paul); B. [Berthold] Riehl, Geschichte des Sittenbildes in der deutschen Kunst bis zum Tode Pieter Breughel des Älteren, Berlin & Stuttgart [Spemann], 1884, citaat p. 89; [verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: F.G. The composition of Bruegel's picture in fact developed from Lucas: The event placed in mountainous country; the rock rising steeply and at the [onleesbaar] a hidden view in the distant land below; also the procession as such, though this treated relief-like [onleesbaar] leading into depth, but some of the figures half hidden by & emerging from the rocks. A painting of the subject by P.B.II strongly influenced by L's print (see Lucas exh. [= B.L.D. (ed.),  Lucas van Leyden en tijdgenoten], Rotterdam 1952, N° 20).</content>
